you're such a selfish man!

130
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,787
You are the worst!

131
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:49,119
What's the matter, Ryo? You don't
look like your usual self.

132
00:08:50,663 --> 00:08:54,166
I understand that you don't want to face
the problem with Kaori, but...

133
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:55,224
Saeko...

134
00:08:56,102 --> 00:08:59,162
Can you investigate the license plate
number of the car that fired at me?

135
00:08:59,405 --> 00:09:00,406
Sure thing.

136
00:09:00,406 --> 00:09:01,873
Sorry.

137
00:09:02,108 --> 00:09:03,743
Ryo, where are you going?

138
00:09:03,743 --> 00:09:05,711
I'm going to get some flowers for Kaori.

139
00:09:21,594 --> 00:09:23,061
Carnations?

140
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,529
Mr. Saeba?

141
00:09:30,536 --> 00:09:32,333
Those carnations, did you
bring them for me?

142
00:09:33,139 --> 00:09:35,505
You told me that you like those, Kaori.

143
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:39,100
Thank you.

144
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:44,150
Mr. Saeba, can I ask some
sensitive questions?

145
00:09:44,150 --> 00:09:44,984
What?

146
00:09:44,984 --> 00:09:48,681
What do you think of Ms. Reika
and Ms. Saeko?

147
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:50,089
What do I think of them?

148
00:09:50,089 --> 00:09:53,422
I can tell that both of them
love you, Mr. Saeba.

149
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,284
Is that the woman's so-called sixth sense?

150
00:09:56,529 --> 00:09:57,663
No, not like that.

151
00:09:57,663 --> 00:10:01,064
I can tell how they're feeling, because
I have someone I love.

152
00:10:02,668 --> 00:10:05,136
I shouldn't have said that.

153
00:10:05,871 --> 00:10:08,808
I can't remember anything
about the man I love,

154
00:10:08,808 --> 00:10:11,971
but he was close to me and
protected me all the time.

155
00:10:12,878 --> 00:10:15,748
But somehow, he never said he loved me.

156
00:10:15,748 --> 00:10:17,716
Even though he knew how I felt about him.

157
00:10:18,718 --> 00:10:22,051
I'm sure that he was just too shy
to say he loves you.

158
00:10:23,022 --> 00:10:24,990
Are you shy just like him?

159
00:10:26,692 --> 00:10:28,159
I...

160
00:10:29,195 --> 00:10:31,561
Men are selfish, I guess.

161
00:10:32,331 --> 00:10:34,856
Oh damn, I have to call my brother.

162
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:38,433
He'll be surprised to hear that
I am in the hospital.

163
00:10:38,671 --> 00:10:41,139
I already told him.

164
00:10:42,074 --> 00:10:44,042
Do you know my brother, Mr. Saeba?

165
00:10:44,276 --> 00:10:46,836
Yes, Makimura is my partner.

166
00:10:47,546 --> 00:10:49,946
He said he's out of town and can't
come to see you today.

167
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:51,739
I see.

168
00:10:53,052 --> 00:10:54,053
He can't come.

169
00:10:54,053 --> 00:10:56,255
Well, I have to go back to work.

170
00:10:56,255 --> 00:10:57,847
Thank you for coming.

171
00:10:58,824 --> 00:11:01,258
Mr. Saeba, can you come
and visit me again?

172
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,806
How was Kaori? Did she remember anything?

173
00:11:17,109 --> 00:11:21,705
No, she believes Makimura is still alive.

174
00:11:22,548 --> 00:11:25,381
She would be happier if
she didn't remember.

175
00:11:26,085 --> 00:11:27,552
What are you talking about, Ryo?!

176
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:31,117
Kaori is trying so hard to remember you!

177
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:33,758
Ryo!

178
00:11:44,804 --> 00:11:48,262
Ryo, what are you going to do
with Kaori's belongings?

179
00:11:48,808 --> 00:11:52,209
I found a vacancy at the apartment
where Makimura used to live.

180
00:11:52,912 --> 00:11:54,379
No way.

181
00:11:54,647 --> 00:11:58,651
As long as she stays with me, things like
this will keep happening to her.

182
00:11:58,651 --> 00:12:02,178
It might cost her not only her memory,
but also her life.

183
00:12:03,489 --> 00:12:04,956
Ryo!

184
00:12:07,793 --> 00:12:10,963
Oh yes, about the car you asked
me about yesterday,

185
00:12:10,963 --> 00:12:14,133
it was a stolen car and
hasn't been found yet.

186
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:15,157
I see.

187
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:21,035
Hello, yes, this is Saeba.

188
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:24,009
It's me, Ryo, shoe-shining Tetsu.

189
00:12:24,009 --> 00:12:26,011
Tetsu, where are you calling from?

190
00:12:26,011 --> 00:12:29,310
In front of your house. I have some
interesting information.

191
00:12:32,852 --> 00:12:36,117
Ryo, you're being targeted by
two strange gangsters.

192
00:12:36,455 --> 00:12:37,683
Two gangsters?

193
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,192
They're mentally unstable somehow.

194
00:12:40,192 --> 00:12:43,286
They want to become famous in the
underground world by killing you.

195
00:12:43,896 --> 00:12:46,626
I see. Where are they?

196
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:49,659
I've heard they live in the warehouse
of a closed factory near Harumi.

197
00:12:50,236 --> 00:12:52,636
They allowed themselves to be traced there.

198
00:12:52,972 --> 00:12:54,707
I guess they're confident they can kill you.

199
00:12:54,707 --> 00:12:56,834
It looks like they want you to come to them.

200
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:59,879
Harumi, a good place to have fun.

201
00:12:59,879 --> 00:13:03,076
One of them is good at shooting, another
one is good at setting traps.

202
00:13:03,682 --> 00:13:06,549
Sounds good. Thank you, Tetsu.

203
00:13:08,687 --> 00:13:10,956
You found out who shot at you, didn't you?

204
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:14,255
Yes, I'm going to go and ask them to
pay Kaori's hospital expenses.

205
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:19,532
Wow, he gets so excited.

206
00:13:19,532 --> 00:13:22,660
I don't think those guys have long to live.

207
00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:30,301
Hello, Kaori.

208
00:13:30,843 --> 00:13:32,936
Ms. Reika, hello.

209
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:35,944
Oh, no, white flowers at the
hospital are bad luck.

210
00:13:36,215 --> 00:13:40,452
Mr. Saeba brought them to me because
I liked them, he said.

211
00:13:40,452 --> 00:13:42,181
He doesn't normally do things like that.

212
00:13:42,555 --> 00:13:44,045
What?

213
00:13:44,456 --> 00:13:46,651
This is a different kind of flower. Look.

214
00:13:48,561 --> 00:13:50,688
The flower language for sweat peas!

215
00:13:51,630 --> 00:13:53,689
What? What is the flower language?

216
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:56,735
Eternal separation.

217
00:13:57,269 --> 00:13:58,771
There's no way Ryo could have known that.

218
00:13:58,771 --> 00:14:04,004
Ms. Reika, please take me to where
Mr. Saeba lives. Please.

219
00:14:16,789 --> 00:14:20,125
Kaori hides her hammers in here.

220
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,593
I wonder if I can have one?

221
00:14:23,262 --> 00:14:24,729
What the hell is this?!

222
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,433
Kaori's belongings are gone!

223
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:29,060
Is this my room?

224
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:32,095
Kaori, are you well enough to go out?

225
00:14:32,938 --> 00:14:34,599
What the hell is going on here, Sister?!

226
00:14:34,807 --> 00:14:36,934
Not me. Ryo did it, but listen, Kaori.

227
00:14:37,276 --> 00:14:40,541
He did this because he's concerned for you.

228
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:42,743
Well, where is Mr. Saeba?

229
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:44,183
He had an urgent matter to take care of.

230
00:14:44,183 --> 00:14:45,317
If you know where he is, tell me.

231
00:14:45,317 --> 00:14:46,807
I'm going to give him another punch!

232
00:14:46,986 --> 00:14:48,544
Calm down.

233
00:14:48,921 --> 00:14:51,290
Ryo went to Harumi because he had
to take care of something.

234
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:52,416
Harumi?!

235
00:14:54,627 --> 00:14:55,924
Kaori, wait!

236
00:14:57,263 --> 00:14:58,230
Kaori!



237
00:15:02,501 --> 00:15:03,968
I have to hear it from him.

238
00:15:04,303 --> 00:15:06,168
I have to hear what he really thinks
directly from him!

239
00:15:11,210 --> 00:15:12,677
She's gone.

240
00:15:23,656 --> 00:15:25,424
Do you think he is really coming, Bro?

241
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,654
I'm sure he will. Watch carefully.

242
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:32,197
After we kill City Hunter, we're gonna be
top class professionals, Brother.

243
00:15:32,197 --> 00:15:33,687
Sure, we will!

244
00:15:35,134 --> 00:15:36,101
Here he comes, Bro.

245
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:37,398
Don't miss this chance!

246
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:44,503
Take your aim carefully.

247
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:50,582
Can he see us?!

248
00:15:51,317 --> 00:15:53,148
What are you doing?
Hurry up and shoot him!

249
00:15:55,087 --> 00:15:56,679
Damn, where did he go?

250
00:15:59,925 --> 00:16:02,359
Stuff happens. Well, let's finish him now.

251
00:16:12,071 --> 00:16:13,272
Brother, did we kill him?

252
00:16:13,272 --> 00:16:16,605
Sure, if he's alive after all those explosive
traps, he's not human.

253
00:16:18,744 --> 00:16:20,211
We did it!

254
00:16:25,384 --> 00:16:26,351
Brother!

255
00:16:31,290 --> 00:16:32,757
What kind of man is he?!

256
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:55,607
Now he'll be the target of a
shooting game for me.

257
00:17:00,652 --> 00:17:02,449
I guess he has given up his life now.

258
00:17:03,555 --> 00:17:04,522
What the hell?!

259
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:13,498
We can't get him. Let's go, Brother.

260
00:17:13,732 --> 00:17:15,893
Damn, in that case, come with me.

261
00:17:23,776 --> 00:17:25,243
This is Mr. Saeba's car.

262
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:35,516
Oil!

263
00:17:36,688 --> 00:17:38,679
Let's start the barbecue party!

264
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,332
Even if you are the City Hunter,
you're finished now.

265
00:17:47,332 --> 00:17:48,299
Who are you?!

266
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:52,771
That woman, she was with
City Hunter the other day.

267
00:17:52,771 --> 00:17:53,738
Get her.

268
00:17:54,673 --> 00:17:55,799
Wait!

269
00:17:56,975 --> 00:17:57,342
Let me go!

270
00:17:57,342 --> 00:17:58,477
Let me go!
